{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, we conclude that the MANCHA3D code is effectively scalable up to several thousands of CPUs.",
    "For 2D simulations there is an optimal subdomain size allowing significant gain in the parallel performance.",
    "For 3D cases it is more efficient to run the code with larger subdomains, avoiding sizes smaller than 25 -30 grid points in each direction.",
    "It should also be kept in mind that frequent saving of big snapshots increases the overall running clock time, regardless of the number of processors used in the simulation.",
    "In this paper, we describe in detail the equations and numerical methods used in the MAN-CHA3D code."
  ]
}